Can't run. CreateTensor doesn't support std::vector<std::array<float, 224 * 224 * 3>>.data() as parameter.
The `TypeToTensorType<T>::type` doesn't support std::array<float, 224 * 224 * 3>.
That can run. but I want predict ins, not ins[0]. It seems this API doesn't support that. Should I follow the https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/1568
I'm not sure what you mean by 'predict ins'. But that was just meant to be an example of how to create a tensor given a shape (and using existing data). What is the error you are getting now?

That will work, though you probably don't want to be making copies of the output_tensors data if you can help it. You also probably don't want to be copying std::array<float, 224*224*3> sized objects by value.

Otherwise, it should work!

Previous code is not batch predict,it's predict one by one. Why `session.Run` return a `std::vector` of `Value` instead of return a `Value`? @RyanUnderhill I thought `session.Run` can predict a lot once a time.
A model can have multiple outputs, the return value of Run() is simply these multiple outputs. If the model has only one output, it's a vector of one item.
@bitnick10 I'm not familiar with Keras's predict. Sorry about the delay, did you already figure this out or do you still have an unresolved question?
@RyanUnderhill ,I can batch predict now,first change symbolic dimension which can check issue 2174 out.
